modules.description: The module provides operations for parsing and managing command-line parameters, including value conversion, metadata-driven declarations, and dynamic configuration resolution. It supports primitive data types (float, string), enums, file paths, and composite structures (lists, arrays, pairs) by parsing and validating values from strings with customizable formatting. These features enable building configurable applications, generating command-line documentation, and handling complex settings from diverse input sources like files or environment variables.

This module provides command-line argument parsing and configuration management with support for primitive and composite data types, including integers, strings, enums, lists, and file paths. It offers typed parameters for configuration values, dynamic resolution of settings from multiple sources, and structured logging through formatted output channels. Concrete use cases include building configurable command-line tools, managing application settings with defaults and overrides, and generating usage documentation from parameter metadata.
